import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    avg_delay_by_origin = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].mean().reset_index()
    avg_delay_by_origin.sort_values('delay', inplace=True)
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(avg_delay_by_origin['origin'], avg_delay_by_origin['delay'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Delay Time (minutes)')
    ax.set_title('What is the average delay time for each origin airport?')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['distance'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Flight Distances')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distances?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['origin_destination'] = data['origin'] + '-' + data['destination']
    origin_destination_counts = data['origin_destination'].value_counts().reset_index()
    origin_destination_counts.columns = ['origin_destination', 'count']
    origin_destination_counts['origin'] = origin_destination_counts['origin_destination'].apply(lambda x: x.split('-')[0])
    origin_destination_counts['destination'] = origin_destination_counts['origin_destination'].apply(lambda x: x.split('-')[1])

    pivot_table = origin_destination_counts.pivot(index='origin', columns='destination', values='count').fillna(0)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 12))
    sns.heatmap(pivot_table, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt='.0f', linewidths=.5)
    plt.title('What is the most common origin-destination pair?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Origin')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.date
    flight_counts = data['date'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    plt.plot(flight_counts.index, flight_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Flight Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Flight Count'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
